<abstract>
            <section>
                <para>As part of a geochemical study of the Commonwealth Glacier in Taylor Valley,
                        Antarctica, two 3-meter snow pits were dug in the accumulation zone and analyzed for 
                        major ions by ion chromatography.  This dataset shows the mean annual atmospheric
                        flux of chloride, sulfate, nitrate, and calcium to the Commonwealth Glacier.  Determination 
                        of the atmospheric flux of these ions to the glacier surface aids in assessing the chemical
                        composition of precipitation to the McMurdo Dry Valleys and the role of glaciers in the
                        geochemical cycles of the region.</para>
            </section>
        </abstract>
